OL,3,CReform crush Labour to secure historic
OL,4,Cwins in Wakefield and Barnsley
OL,6,FLabour has lost control of the
OL,7,Fcouncils in both Barnsley and
OL,8,FWakefield for the first time in their
OL,9,Fhistory after crushing defeats to
OL,10,FReform.
OL,12,FThe party had enjoyed majorities in
OL,13,Fboth the South and West Yorkshire
OL,14,Fboroughs since their formation in 1974
OL,15,Fand went into Thursday's election
OL,16,Fholding 46 of the 63 seats in Barnsley
OL,17,Fand 48 of the 63 in Wakefield.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G1/7
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,366,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F365A1778415071
OL,3,CReform crush Labour to secure historic
OL,4,Cwins in Wakefield and Barnsley
OL,6,FBut by Friday evening Reform, who did
OL,7,Fnot have a single seat on either
OL,8,Fcouncil until the vote, had secured
OL,9,Fthe 32 seats needed to claim control
OL,10,Fof both.
OL,12,FDenise Jeffery, the defeated Labour
OL,13,Fleader of Wakefield Council, launched
OL,14,Fstinging criticism of Sir Keir Starmer
OL,15,Ffollowing the result.
OL,17,FShe said: "I put the blame squarely at
OL,18,Fthe door of the Prime Minister.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/7
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,366,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F365A1778415071
OL,3,CReform crush Labour to secure historic
OL,4,Cwins in Wakefield and Barnsley
OL,6,F"On the doorstep, people were saying
OL,7,Fthey wouldn't vote for us because Keir
OL,8,FStarmer was toxic.
OL,10,F"There'd been so many mistakes and I
OL,11,Fdon't think it's the Labour brand, I
OL,12,Fjust think it's the Starmer brand."
OL,14,FJohn Thomas, Reform Branch chairman
OL,15,Ffor Pontefract, Castleford, and
OL,16,FNormanton, told the Local Democracy
OL,17,FReporting Service: "It's gone far
OL,18,Fbetter than we could have hoped for."
OL,20,FHe said it was :"beyond out wildest
OL,21,Fimaginations".
OL,26,@yD@TOU
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/7
